# Core — eye-budget Monorepo

## Repo Layout

```
eye-budget/
├── frontend/   # Next.js 14, App Router, TypeScript strict, npm
└── backend/    # FastAPI, Pydantic, psycopg2, Celery, Python 3.x
```

No monorepo tool (no Turborepo/Nx). Each app has its own package manager / dependency file.

## Language Boundaries

- TypeScript lives exclusively in `frontend/`. Python lives exclusively in `backend/`.
- Never introduce Python patterns (dataclasses, snake_case models) into TypeScript files.
- Never introduce JavaScript/TypeScript patterns (callbacks, promises) into Python files.

## API Contract — both sides must stay in sync

When adding or changing an endpoint, update **all four** of:
1. `backend/src/main.py` — route definition
2. `backend/src/data.py` — Pydantic request/response models
3. `frontend/app/api/<resource>/route.ts` — Next.js proxy route handler
4. `frontend/lib/api.ts` + `frontend/lib/types.ts` — typed client function + Zod schema

## UI Primitives

Before creating any UI component, check `frontend/components/ui/index.ts`.
The design system already provides: Button, Input, Textarea, Modal, ConfirmDeleteModal,
Card, Badge (StatusBadge, SourceBadge, MatchBadge, CountBadge), Pill, FilterTabs,
PageHeader, SectionLabel, ThreeDotsMenu, Amount, NavLink, PrevNextNav, DateInput.

Do not create parallel or duplicate primitives.

## UI Language

All user-facing strings are in **Polish**. Do not introduce English copy in page/component text.

## Secrets & Credentials

- **Never read or modify `.env`** (contains real DB, OpenAI, MinIO credentials).
- Use `.env.example` as the reference for available environment variables.
- `backend/yoyo.ini` contains live DB credentials — treat it as secret.

## Request Flow (summary)

```
Browser → "use client" page → useQuery/useMutation → lib/api.ts
       → /api/... route handler → lib/proxy.ts → FastAPI backend
       → App() → service → repository → PostgreSQL
```

## Canonical References

- `frontend/components/ui/index.ts` — full list of available UI primitives
- `backend/src/main.py` — canonical route structure
- `backend/src/app.py` — App class wiring pattern
- `docker-compose.yml` — all runtime services (Redis, Soketi, backend, celery-worker)
- `.env.example` — all required environment variables
